The paper deals with the study of k-monotone functions, which are a natural generalization of monotone functions, and have been recently studied in circuit complexity, PAC learning, and cryptography. The paper specifically focuses on the parametrized property testing model, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The study of k-monotone functions also involves the analysis of hypercube non-adaptive testing, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of distinguishing functions that are k-monotone from functions that are far from being k-monotone, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the study of patterns and dependencies in functions, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
